commit.message:
reimplement find_bm() using std::search

Use std::search() to implement find_bm() instead of using a
local implementation of Boyer-Moore.

Avoids integer overflow reported in issue #31 and PR #31.
Should fix build problem in issue #7.

std::search is also faster for the test program in issue #31
on a system with an Intel Xeon E-2224 CPU:
- gcc 8.5, find_bm(): 3.16s
- g++ 8.5, std::search: 2.40s
- g++ 13, std::search: 2.16s

Experiments using the C++17 std::boyer_moore_searcher or
std::boyer_moore_horspool_searcher were also slower than
std::search in this experiment.

mimeentity.h: support c++03 again

Disabling copy constructors with =delete is only supported since c++11.
If pre c++11, declare but don't define the constructors.

base64.h: fix -Werror=maybe-uninitialized more portably

When fixing -Werror=maybe-uninitialized, use memset() instead
of member initialisation, as the latter requires C++11.
Improve my previous fix on 2023-04-07.

Replace deprecated std::iterator

C++17 deprecated std::iterator.

For backwards compatibility, typedef the members that std::iterator
used to provide:
    iterator_category, value_type, difference_type, pointer, reference

Replace deprecated std::unary_function

C++11 deprecated std::unary_function and C++17 removed it.

For backwards compatibility, typedef the members that std::unary_function
used to provide:
    argument_type, result_type
cutee: remove path from __FILE__ appended to filenames

test: fix parallel build of *.cutee.cxx

Add missing dependency on cutee for the rule for %.cutee.cxx.
Directly modify Makefile.in instead of regenerating.

Fix -Werror=register

register is deprecated in C++17
Fix -Werror=maybe-uninitialized
Fix -Werror=unused-variable
Fix -Werror=literal-suffix
Fix -Werror=sequence-point
Fix -Werror=maybe-uninitialized
Fix -Werror=char-subscripts
Fix -Werror=sign-compare

commit.message:
Modify wrong memory reference

 - If input is a string of only spaces,
   index becomes -1 during removes trailing spaces operation,
   referencing the wrong memory.
 - If the referenced memory value is a space,
   out_of_range occurs
   because -1 is entered in the erase function pos parameter.
 - Modify to return immediately if the input value is empty
   after the removes leading spaces operation.
